This is Parent_C applying again in Round 10 for your remaining place. Nursery_C remains our second choice overall and our top available option.

Given that we are now late in the process and Nursery_C is the only nursery still unmatched, if there is no higher-priority family actively applying/confirming this round, we would be very grateful if you could finalize the offer to us. We are ready to accept immediately and complete all enrollment steps right away.

Thank you very much for your consideration.
Sincerely,
Parent_C
conversation.thought: Only Nursery_C remains unmatched and it is my 2nd true choice, so I should continue to apply rather than talk. Nursery_C has repeatedly rejected me because they are waiting for higher-priority families (Parent_D, Parent_E, Parent_A, Parent_B) who might still apply. At Round 10, with all other nurseries already matched and only Nursery_C left, it is less likely that a higher-priority family will newly become available and apply here. I will submit a concise, firm application emphasizing immediate confirmation and asking them to finalize if no higher-priority applicant is actively in the pipeline this round.

conversation.message:
Dear Parent_C,

Thank you for your Round 10 application and for your continued, clear commitment to Nursery_C.

Given the stage of the process and our need to finalize our remaining place, we are able to offer you the place at Nursery_C this round. Please reply with your confirmation and we will proceed immediately with the enrollment steps and paperwork.

Kind regards,
Nursery_C Admissions

[ACCEPT]
conversation.thought: Nursery_C has 1 seat and true priority order is D > E > A > B > C. Only Parent_C applied this round; no higher-priority applicants are currently engaging with us. Given we are at round 10 and Nursery_C is the only nursery still unmatched, continued waiting risks ending unmatched, which is worse than filling with an eligible parent (Parent_C is on our list). Parent_C has repeatedly demonstrated strong commitment and immediate acceptance. Accepting now secures a match rather than holding out for unlikely late applications from higher-priority parents who have their own preferred options and may already be matched elsewhere.
